snippet.title: Automate Performance Monitoring for Micro Frontend Apps - Amit Batra
snippet.description:
Automate Performance Monitoring for Micro Frontend Apps

Leveraging lighthouse CI and Puppeteer to build a tool that continuously monitors the performance of applications behind authentication. At Brevo we build a culture where performance is not an afterthought. This talk will detail our journey of improving performance over the year and how you can set up your own CI/CD pipeline to monitor page performance before it goes into production.

Speaker Details 

Amit Batra Lead Engineer Frontend, Brevo

snippet.title: Web Workers - Little Minions At Work for Optimizing Performance | Nida Shaikh
snippet.description:
React’s single-threaded-ness is very unnoticeable in our day-to-day applications since the UI renders really fast. However, our UI can be easily stumped if our app is computationally heavy. We'll see how web workers can boost your application’s performance, offering multithreading capabilities.


About Speaker 

Hi, I'm Nida Shaikh, and I'm a Full Stack Software Engineer at Contentstack, with a passion for elegant and scalable solutions. I dive head-first into everything web and my goal is to make development a little bit easier for us all devs. When I'm not coding, I love to read, journal, explore new places, make specialty coffee and pet my cats.

snippet.title: Encrypting Data in the Browser - Exploring Web Crypto APIs | Aakansha Doshi
snippet.description:
Encrypting data in the Browser - Exploring Web Crypto APIs

In this talk Aakansha will be deep-diving into the world of Web Crypto APIs, starting from key generation, various encryption algorithms, implementation techniques, and more. The session will include live demos, coding examples, and a fun side project as well.

snippet.title: Navigating the Shift SDLC’s Transformation into AI-Driven Engineering  | Rakesh Ravuri
snippet.description:
Navigating the Shift: SDLC’s Transformation into AI-Driven Engineering

The topic revolves around the transformative impact of Generative AI on the traditional Software Development Life Cycle (SDLC). As we step into an era where AI is not just a tool but a collaborator, the entire landscape of software engineering is undergoing a seismic shift.

This theme underscores the need for a paradigm shift in our approach to software development, embracing AI as an integral part of the engineering process and preparing for a future where AI and human ingenuity work in tandem to push the boundaries of what’s possible in technology.


About the Speaker 

Rakesh Ravuri is a CTO & SVP in Publicis Sapient's Engineering Capability. As the CTO for Publicis Sapient, Rakesh heads engineering strategy and engineering capability development in India. Rakesh also plays the role of engineering lead globally for all Publicis Sapient's Retail engagements. This is Rakesh's second innings at Sapient. He has served in various engineering roles for Publicis Sapient's partners in Retail & Financial industries, delivering internet scale e-commerce solutions, high frequency trading and real time risk evaluation systems. He has experience leading cross geography teams and proven track record of enabling business outcomes working in a GDD model. Prior to joining Sapient, Rakesh worked as Director of Technology at Amazon led the team to help roll out Amazon Shipping product in four countries and was Chief Architect at Tesco for their online systems and helped rollout their international groceries ecommerce platform in nine countries. He holds a Bachelor's Degree in Engineering from NIT Surathkal and a Master's Degree specializing in robotics from Texas A&M.

More on the React India Website - https://www.reactindia.io/

snippet.title: Abracadabra: The Vanishing Network | Kent C Dodds @KentCDodds-vids | React India 2024
snippet.description:
⁠Kent C. Dodds( @KentCDodds-vids  ) is a world renowned speaker, teacher, and trainer and he's actively involved in the open source community as a maintainer and contributor of hundreds of popular npm packages. He is the creator of EpicWeb.dev, the Epic Stack, EpicReact.Dev and TestingJavaScript.com. He's an instructor on egghead.io and Frontend Masters. He's also a live streamer, podcaster, and conference organizer. Kent is married and the father of five kids.

About the session

Abracadabra: The Vanishing Network

The network that stands between our server and the client is what causes the most complexity in our development process. Whether it be the initial UI we generate on the server, the API calls we make as the user navigates around, or the form submissions our user makes, keeping the application responsive and up-to-date is a massive chore.

⁠What would it be like if all of that complexity just disappeared? Freaking great, that's what it would be like. And React Server Components and Actions are what's making that possible. In this talk, we'll look into how that's happening and how we can take advantage of this amazing developer experience to deliver even better user experiences.


More details on our website - www.reactindia.io

snippet.title: What's next for the React Compiler?  - Sathya Gunasekaran
snippet.description:
The React Compiler was open-sourced at React Conf earlier this year, marking a significant milestone. Since then, we've implemented numerous improvements and optimizations. This talk will examine the valuable community feedback that has shaped these enhancements and explore the new optimizations that improve both performance and developer experience. We'll also discuss the next steps in the evolution of the React Compiler and the open source release process.

Sathya is a software engineer on the React core team at Meta. Previously, he worked on the V8 JavaScript compiler at Google.

snippet.title: Remote Talk: Concurrent Rendering in React - Mithun Devarajulu & Alok Kumar
snippet.description:
Discover how React's concurrent rendering feature improves application responsiveness and efficiency. By allowing React to handle multiple tasks simultaneously, concurrent rendering ensures that high-priority interactions are addressed immediately, keeping the interface fluid during intensive operations. We'll cover key concepts like interruptible rendering, which pauses tasks to prioritize user actions and optimizes performance. Additionally, features like Suspense and transitions help manage asynchronous data loading and non-urgent updates, delivering a smoother and responsive user experience in modern web applications.

Speaker Details:
Mithun Devarajulu
Software Architect, Epam

Alok Kumar
Senior Software Engineer, Epam
